Terraform vs Ansible
************************
What is the difference between Terraform and Ansible? Terraform is an open-source platform designed to provision cloud infrastructure,
while Ansible is an open-source configuration management tool focused on the configuration of that infrastructure.

terraform vs cloudformation
***************************
 CloudFormation is developed by AWS and only manages AWS resources. Terraform is developed by HashiCorp and can manage resources across a wide range of cloud vendors.

https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6XT0grm_TfgdaAjTmLb4QedMCCMQHISm (best)
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yRcf_vrp3v4 (terraform using CDK)

terraform vs cdk
***************************
If you have only AWS in your environment, and the infra is small, CDK should be enough. Terraform is more suited for complex environments, and if you already use it as the IaC tool to manage other infrastructure.
https://medium.com/@kansvignesh/aws-cdk-vs-terraform-738c39d91f7a
https://www.nclouds.com/blog/aws-cdk-for-terraform/
